==English==
===Nominal phrase===
'''intentional walk''' (plural: initentional walks)

#{{baseball}} When the fourth ball is thrown to a batter on purpose in order to face the next batter 
#: ''Jones was given an '''intentional walk''' in order to face Smith.''

===Transitive verb phrase===
'''intentional walk'''

#{{baseball}} to give a batter a fourth ball on purpose in order to face the next batter 
#: ''They '''intentionally walked''' Jones as there was a better match-up against Smith.''